title: AttributeError: module 'keras.backend.tensorflow_backend' has no attribute '_SESSION'
body:
First steps with SHAP on a simple MNIST classifier network:

```
net = keras.models.Sequential([
    keras.layers.Input(shape=(28,28)),
    keras.layers.Flatten(),
    keras.layers.Dense(128, activation="relu"),
    keras.layers.Dropout(0.2),
    keras.layers.Dense(n_classes, activation="softmax")
])
net.compile(
    optimizer='adam',
    loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy',
    metrics=['accuracy']
)
net.fit(
    X_train, 
    y_train, 
    epochs=10, 
)

background = X_train[numpy.random.choice(X_train.shape[0], 100, replace=False)]

shap.DeepExplainer(net, background)
```
